## Dynamic Route Parameters (Next.js 15+)
### Page Components
```typescript
// Type definition
interface PageProps {
  params: Promise<{
    paramName: string;
  }>;
}

// Usage in page component
export default async function Page({ params }: PageProps) {
  const { paramName } = await params;
  // Use paramName...
}

// Usage in generateMetadata
export async function generateMetadata({ params }: PageProps) {
  const { paramName } = await params;
  return {
    title: `Page ${paramName}`,
  };
}
```

### Route Handlers
```typescript
export async function GET(
  request: NextRequest,
  { params }: { params: Promise<{ paramName: string }> }
) {
  const { paramName } = await params;
  // Use paramName...
}
```

### Key Rules
1. Always type params as a Promise
2. Always await params before accessing properties
3. Update both page components and API routes
4. Apply in generateMetadata and other metadata functions
5. Don't access params properties directly without awaiting

